Iranian students are ready to die for their country's nuclear program.
They created a living shield
Several hundred college students formed a human shield around a nuclear facility in Iran.
With their gesture, they want to express their support for their country's nuclear program against a possible Israeli attack.
Students prayed outside the building at noon on Tuesday and then chanted death to the U.S. and Israel.
