It holds the most patents of any U.S. tech company, and five of its employees have won Nobel Prizes.
Her inventions include an ATM, a payment card, a financial swap, a barcode and a floppy disk.
IBM, at about $220 billion, became the second-largest tech company by market capitalization this year (first being Apple), overtaking Microsoft for the first time since 1996.
Looking ahead
