The French are no more sick than elsewhere in Europe.
Let's first look at a few official figures.
According to the Caisse nationale d'assurance maladie (CNAM), more than €237 million in daily compensation was paid out in 2006.
According to the French Institute for Health Research and Documentation, daily reimbursements accounted for 5% of health spending in 2008, with €11.3 billion.
