The terrorist front extends from the Sahara to Nigeria
Paris is concerned about ties between al-Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb and Boko Haram.
Long-standing suspicions that there are links between the terrorist group Al-Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb (AQMI) and the Nigerien sect Boko Haram are confirmed.
On Sunday, Algeria's deputy foreign minister, Abdelkader Messahel, even admitted that Algeria had "gained certainty" from now on.
